description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Clinical Fellow (ST3+ Level) to join our Acute Medicine team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;These are exciting times for Acute Medicine and the post holder will join an established team who are further developing our SDEC, Short Stay and Acute Medical Services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be supported to develop their medical career and will be expected to provide senior cover, supporting junior colleagues.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are investing heavily in our Acute Medical services and as such, the rota will change as we recruit and develop the services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post is not recognised for training however support in developing a Learning Portfolio and regular educational appraisal with a Consultant Educator will be available.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is a Teaching Hospital, linked to the London University and is also the Cancer Centre for South Essex which is part of the Essex Cancer network. This busy DGH serves a population of 338,800. We currently employ 4,567 wte staff with a total complement of 190 Consultant staff. Situated in the South East of England, with excellent rail links to London. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Trust has an excellent Postgraduate Medical Centre which carries a full programme of events and offers access to a Medical Library.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Alfred FawoleJob titleClinical LeadEmail addressalfred.fawole@southend.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
